		<div class="comment_text"><p>Just so you guys know, if you ever want to force a plugin to install on a version Firefox version that isn't supported. Then download the plugin (i.e. go to Save as...) it will be a .xpi file.</p><p>A .xpi file is a .zip file just renamed, so you can open it and inside there is an xml document that stores the min and max FF versions, just change the max version to the version you are running (e.g 3) then save the .xpi and drag it onto a Firefox window, the plugin will install as normal.</p></div>
