		<div class="comment_header">
		Comment <a href="#c_1713674618">13</a> by T.J.
		posted on 12/20/2007 at 8:19 PM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>Wanna run to side by side?  No matter what OS you are using, right click (or the OS equivilent) on the launcher, click properties, and you'll see the "target" or "action" property (it will be a path to the application).  Enter this:</p><p>"c:\path\to\firefox\firefox.exe" -p something -no-remote<br>/path/to/firefox/firefox -p testprofile2 -no-remote</p><p>You can use different profiles (after the -p flag) to load up the browser with its default settings, (or settings for that profile).  The -no-remote make it ignore whether there is already a firefox version running or not (doesn't work on FF 1.5 and below).  So you can run FF 1.5, 2, another 2, and 3 all simultaneously.</p></div>
	</div>
</div>
		
